1. Vocabulary selection (CEFR levels A1–A2–B1)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The choice of which words appear at each level is informed by the publicly
available official word lists ("Wortlisten") published by the Goethe-Institut
for the Goethe-Zertifikat A1 (Start Deutsch 1), A2, and B1 examinations.

These lists are used here only as a factual reference for vocabulary scope.
The English translations and the pseudo-phonetic pronunciation hints in this
app are original to the project and are NOT taken from those publications.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Example sentences  —  original content
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The German example sentences (example_de) and their English translations
(example_en) shipped in the data files are ORIGINAL CONTENT authored for this
project. Earlier versions reproduced sentences from the Goethe-Institut /
Hueber Verlag / telc / ÖSD Wortliste publications (copyrighted,
"urheberrechtlich geschützt"); all of those have been replaced.

All 2,627 example sentences across A1/A2/B1 were re-authored and verified:
  - scripts/check_example_originality.py reports 0 verbatim matches (and no
    6-word shingle copies) against the official source PDFs;
  - scripts/check_grammar_languagetool.py independently grammar-checks them
    with the offline LanguageTool engine.

These sentences are therefore original to the project and are not subject to
the source publishers' copyright. See
PRODUCTION_READINESS_AUDIT_2026-07-01.md (§3) for details.

